description: Launched in September 2021 as a collaboration between the National Aeronautics and Space Administration (NASA) and United States Geological Survey (USGS), Landsat-9 continues the Landsat program to monitor, understand and manage land resources crucial for sustaining human life. Landsat-9 mission objectives include the collection and archival of moderate-resolution multispectral data, to be made freely available to worldwide users.
title: Landsat-9
